extends layout

block pagehead
  title Fontes Anglo-Saxonici - Pinned
  script(src=baseUrl+"javascripts/pinnedpage.js")

block content
  div(class="row")
      h1(class="page-heading col-8 offset-col-2") Pinned
  div(class="row")
      div(class="col-6 offset-col-2 main-text-content" role="main")
          p It looks like you haven't pinned any entries yet. To pin an entry, click the "pin" icon on the left of a record. Try clicking on the pin in the example record below.

          button(class="example-record accordion col-12 row")
              span(class="col-1 col-s-1 col-xs-2 pin")
              span(class="col-10 col-s-10 col-xs-10") Example Record
              span(class="col-1 col-s-1 col-xs-2 entry-arrow")
          span

          p You can pin entries from various searches so you can collect all entries you are interested in a centralised location. These records will be stored until you unpin them or clear your browser's storage.

